                <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="../img/labor.jpg" alt="Featurette 2">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <h2 class="featurette-heading">Labor <span class="text-muted"> Code.</span></h2>
                <p class="lead">Morocco's labor code is characterized by its compliance with the international standards as set out in the UN conventions. Protected rights include: Freedom of association and the effective adoption of the organizing and collective bargaining law, the prohibition of all forms of work by compulsion among others.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- ./Featurette 2 -->

        <hr id="copyright" class="featurette-divider">

        <!-- Featurette 3 -->
        <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <h2 class="featurette-heading">Copyright and <span class="text-muted">Related Rights</span></h2>
                <p class="lead">These measures aim to synchronize the national legislation with the commitments made by Morocco in terms of Treaties and international agreements such as the World Organization's (WTO) TRIPS Agreement (Trade-Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights) and Internet WIPO Treaties. The Moroccan Copyright Office, under the responsibilty of the Ministry of Communications, is responsible for the protection and exploitation of copyright and related rights.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="../img/copyright-symbol.jpg" alt="Featurette 3">
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- ./Featurette 3 -->

        <hr id="competition" class="featurette-divider">

        <!-- Featurette 2 -->
        <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="../img/competition.jpg" alt="Featurette 2">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <h2 class="featurette-heading">Competition <span class="text-muted">Law.</span></h2>
                <p class="lead">The law prohibits anti-competitive practices that could prevent, restrict or distort competition in the national market. These practices are: agreements, abuse of a dominant position or the abuse of economic dependence. The penalties provided by law are mainly financial. The levels of penalties are determined based on the seriousness of the offense and the harm suffered by the market or by the operators and the circumstances that justify them.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- ./Featurette 4 -->

        <hr id="protection" class="featurette-divider">

        <!-- Featurette 5 -->
        <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <h2 class="featurette-heading">Personnal Data <span class="text-muted">Protection</span></h2>
                <p class="lead">The law defines, among others and accurately, the right of access to databases containing personal data, to oppose certain treatments, request correction of erroneous data or deletion of outdated data or that the purpose of the treatment was performed. With the adoption of the law 09-08, Morocco is among the first Arab and African country with such a comprehensive system of protection, and ranks among the safest destinations from the perspective of the flow of personal data</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <img class="featurette-image img-responsive" src="../img/dataprotection.jpg" alt="Featurette 3">
